    "Reason: The GitHub Actions runtime is ephemeral. Tier 2/3 events require",
    "an approval window the runner can't host. Routing this event through",
    "the Worker template instead is the safe path \u2014 it persists drafts in",
    "Workers KV, fires the email/CLI/web approval surfaces, and dispatches",
    "after operator approval.",
    "",
    "Options:",
    "  1. Configure this noteworthiness as Tier 1 in your broadcast.config.json",
    "     `tierPolicy.minor = 'tier1.auto-post'` (only if your release notes",
    "     are template-driven with no LLM-generated prose).",
    "  2. Stand up the Cloudflare Worker template:",
    "     `pnpm create broadcast-worker my-broadcaster`",
    "     The Worker receives the same release webhook and routes through Tier 2.",
    "  3. Run the CLI manually after release lands:",
    "     `npx @sizl/broadcast post --event github-release@<tag>`",
    "",
